{
  "answer": "**Kātyāyana Smṛti** and **Viṣṇu Smṛti** contain rules concerning the ordeal of fire (*agni*), or *dharmaparīkṣā* by fire, as a judicial test in cases of theft, denial of debt, or other disputes. These texts, as Dharmaśāstras, prescribe when to apply it (e.g., based on the amount stolen or caste), procedural details, and prohibitions (e.g., avoiding it for certain professions or conditions).[^1][^2][^3][^4][^5]\n\nA third work, **Traité de Législation: VOL II** by Charles Comte, briefly describes (rather than prescribes) a fire ordeal involving holding a burning coal among certain African peoples as an alternative to poison, chosen by priests.[^6] No other works in the corpus discuss it.\n\n[^1]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 32, [p-c8377d](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/32/translation/#p-c8377d). \"For a loss of eighty, one should indeed administer the ordeal of fire.\"\n[^2]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 33, [p-9f579b](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/33/translation/#p-9f579b). \"To a Kshatriya, the ordeal of fire...\"\n[^3]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 33, [p-c24edd](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/33/translation/#p-c24edd). \"One should not apply the ordeal of fire to blacksmiths...\"\n[^4]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 9, [p-d2dfbe](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/09/translation/#p-d2dfbe). \"The ordeal of fire shall not be administered to lepers, the infirm, or blacksmiths.\"\n[^5]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 11, [p-082f71](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/11/translation/#p-082f71). \"Now, the ordeal of fire (*agni*).\"\n[^6]: Charles Comte, *Traité de Législation: VOL II*, Chapter 27, [p-908516](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-ii-20331d/27-des-rapports-observes-entre-les-moyens-d-existence/translation/#p-908516).",
